<p><strong>Overview</strong></p>
<p>
This is a library of retro gaming manuals sourced from a variety of websites and processed for optimal viewing.  These manuals have been:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Converted into a consistent PDF format</li>
  <li>Auto-rotated, when appropriate</li>
  <li>OCR'd</li>
  <li>Cleaned</li>
  <li>Named according to no-intro and redump DATs (using the parent, non-clone title + languages)</li>
</ul>
<p>
Every manual has been:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Inspected for quality to archive the highest-quality manual available (up to 600dpi)</li>
  <li>Inspected for the list of languages available within it</li>
</ul>
<p>
This library is primarily used for the <a href="https://github.com/obrie/retrokit" rel="nofollow">retrokit</a> project, but is additionally meant as a means to track retro gaming manuals, where they're sourced from, and have a central community-managed source for them.
</p>

