<p><strong>Arcade Manuals</strong></p>
<p>
As far as I've been able to find, there doesn't exist any form of player instruction manuals for arcade games.  You can attempt to cut out instructions from bezel artwork, but that's a very time consuming process that I haven't undertaken.  There *do* exist owner manuals for the arcade cabinets themselves, but that's not helpful to most players.
</p>
<p></p>
<p>
As an alternative, I've built manuals based on several sources:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Cabinets from <a href="https://www.progettosnaps.net/cabinets/" rel="nofollow">progrettosnaps</a></li>
  <li>Flyers from <a href="https://www.progettosnaps.net/flyers/" rel="nofollow">progrettosnaps</a></li>
  <li>Select artwork from <a href="https://www.progettosnaps.net/artworks/" rel="nofollow">progrettosnaps</a></li>
  <li>Game initialization data from <a href="https://www.progettosnaps.net/gameinit/" rel="nofollow">progrettosnaps</a></li>
</ul>
<p>
The generated manuals aren't perfect, but I felt having some form of instructions was better
than nothing.
</p>
<p>
If anyone has better sources or wants to build better manuals, I'd fully support that effort.
</p>

